-- Ferrer Sweeps Past Anderson in Fourth Round Match at French Open
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2013-06-02T11:34:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-02/ferrer-sweeps-past-anderson-in-fourth-round-match-at-french-open.html
Fifth-seeded  David Ferrer  defeated
South Africa’s Kevin Anderson in straight sets in the fourth
round of tennis’s French Open.  The Spaniard won 6-3, 6-1, 6-1.  Today, top-seeded American Serena Williams will take on
Roberta Vinci of Italy, and second-seeded Roger Federer of
Switzerland will play Gilles Simon of France.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  